title: Ursa Major Engine To Be Used On Astra Rocket 4
summary: Ursa Major CEO, Joe Laurienti, says that the partnership with Astra “marks an important industry milestone in outsourcing propulsion to unlock growth and innovation for launch providers”

title: First ispace lunar lander feared lost
summary: Controllers lost contact with a lunar lander developed by a Japanese company moments before its scheduled touchdown, raising fears the spacecraft crashed during its final descent.

title: NASA Retires Mineral Mapping Instrument on Mars Orbiter
summary: One of six instruments aboard the agency’s Mars Reconnaissance Orbiter, CRISM produced global maps of minerals on the Red Planet’s surface.

title: Japanese lander appears to fail just before touchdown on the Moon [Updated]
summary: This lunar landing is at the vanguard of a number of private landing attempts.

title: Japanese ispace moon landing attempt falls short at ‘very end,’ CEO says
summary: Japanese lunar exploration company ispace attempted to land its first cargo mission on the moon on Tuesday, but lost communication with the spacecraft and has deemed the attempt unsuccessful, CEO Takeshi Hakamada said.

title: NASA Announces Student Winners of Power to Explore Challenge
summary: NASA selected three winners out of nine finalists in the second annual Power to Explore Challenge, a national competition for elementary through high school students featuring the power of radioisotopes for space exploration.

title: Connecting the Dots | SES-Intelsat merger would face uphill regulatory struggle
summary: Plenty of operational synergies await SES and Intelsat if the world’s largest fixed satellite service providers can craft a merger able to clear regulatory scrutiny.

title: Hydrosat collects $20 million in investment and grants
summary: Hydrosat received $20 million in government grants and investment for its campaign to measure water stress in plants and other indicators of climate change.

title: Quantum Space moves up development of Ranger transfer vehicle
summary: Quantum Space is accelerating work on a transfer vehicle designed to take payloads to both geostationary orbit and cislunar space to support growing demand from commercial and government customers.
